08243nam a22011775i 9783110688306DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2021950451  a97831106883067 a10.1515/97831106883062doi  a(DE-B1597)541529  a(OCoLC)1306058726  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE00aP165b.M48 2022. 7aLAN0160002bisacsh04a41500aMetaphorical Conceptualizations :b(Inter)Cultural Perspectives /ced. by Ulrike Schröder, Milene Mendes de Oliveira, Adriana Maria Tenuta. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (VI, 343 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aApplications of Cognitive Linguistics [ACL] ,x1861-4078 ;v4500tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tSection I: Theoretical and methodological reflections on metaphorical conceptualizations -- tExtended conceptual metaphor theory: the cognition-context interface -- tCritical reflections on the use of corpora for cross-varietal metaphor research -- tSection II: Cultural metaphorical conceptualizations -- tIndexicalization and lexicalization of event-based time intervals in Huni Kuĩ, Awetý, and Kamaiurá -- tResemblance metaphor and metonymy in the ethnozoological lexicon of the Amazonian language Aguaruna -- tMetaphorical and cultural conceptualizations in Guyanese newspaper English: novel insights and methodological approaches -- tSection III: Cross-cultural metaphorical conceptualizations -- tThe ‘Olympic Spirit’ from a cross-cultural perspective: a cognitive-pragmatic analysis -- tMetaphor, emotion, and intralinguistic cultural variation: metaphors of anger in European and Brazilian Portuguese -- tPrototypical and metaphorical uses for locative deixis in Brazilian Portuguese and American English: a verbo-gestural data analysis -- tOf wars and vengeance goddesses: metaphorical conceptualizations of Sars-CoV-2 -- tSection IV: Intercultural metaphorical conceptualizations -- tConceptual fluency and meaning negotiation in the German as a Foreign Language classroom: a multimodal analysis of teacher-student interactions -- tHow interculture is built on the common ground of alterity experience: a cognitivemultimodal approach to talk-in-interaction -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe book deals with the important shift that has been heralded in cognitive linguistics from mere universal matters to cultural and situational variation. The discussions examine cognitive and cultural linguistics’ theories in relation to the following areas of research: (i) metaphorical conceptualization; (ii) the influence of culture on metaphor, metonymy and conceptual blends; (iii) the impact of culture and cognition on metaphorical lexis; (iv) the interface of pragmatics and cognition when metaphor is studied in situ, that is, in face-to-face as well as in virtual multimodal interaction; (v) the application of insights from metaphorical conceptualizations to language teaching, and (vi) recent methods for revealing (inter)cultural metaphorical conceptualizations (corpus-based approaches, gesture studies, etc.). The book brings together cognitive, functional, and (inter)cultural approaches.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aLinguisticsxStudy and teaching. 0aLinguistics. 0aMetaphorxSocial aspects. 4aInterkulturelle Kommunikation. 4aMetaphor. 4aMetonymie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Semantics.2bisacsh  aCultural Linguistics.  aIntercultural Communication.  aMetaphor.  aMetonymy.1 aAvelar, Maíra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernande